              "description": {
                "paragraph": [
                  "Apple AirTag is an easy way to keep track of your stuff. Attach one to your keys, slip another one in your backpack. And just like that, they're on your radar in the Find My app. AirTag has your back. Only you can see where your AirTag is. Your location data and history are never stored on the AirTag itself. Devices that relay the location of your AirTag also stay anonymous, and that location data is encrypted every step of the way. So not even Apple knows the location of your AirTag or the identity of the device that helps find it."
                ],
                "descriptionLineSize": 2,
                "bullets": [
                  "Attach an AirTag to your keys, wallet, backpack anything you might lose track of. If you misplace something, just use the Find My app to locate it.",
                  "Each round AirTag is small and lightweight, features precision-etched polished stainless steel, and is IP67 water- and dust-resistant.",
                  "An AirTag can be shared with up to five people, so friends and family can keep track of items everyone uses.",
                  "Made of 100% recycled tin in the solder of the main logic board, comes in black with white",
                  "You can play a sound on the built-in speaker by going to the new Items tab in the Find My app",
                  "If your tracker is nearby, your iPhone can lead you straight to it with Precision Finding, you'll see the distance to your tracker and the direction to head in, all thanks to Ultra Wideband technology",
                  "Precision Finding compatible with: iPhone 11/11 Pro/11 Pro Max/12/12 mini/12 Pro/12 Pro Max",
                  "Can be put into Lost Mode; then, when it's detected by a device in the network, you'll automatically get a notification, or set it so someone can get your contact info by tapping your tracker with an NFC-capable smartphone",
                  "One-tap setup instantly connects the device with your iPhone or iPad; enter a name, attach it to the item you want to track, and you're good to go",
                  "Designed to keep going more than a year on a standard battery you can easily replace",
                  "Bluetooth connectivity for proximity finding",
                  "Apple-designed U1 chip for Ultra Wideband and Precision Finding",
                  "NFC tap for Lost Mode",
                  "Product is mercury-, BFR-, PVC-, and beryllium-free",
                  "Compatible with iPhone and iPod touch models with iOS 14.5 or later, iPad models with iPadOS 14.5 or later",
                  "Meets or exceeds IP67 under IEC 60529 standard",
                  "Size: 0.31\"H x 1.26\"Dia.",
                  "Pack contains four trackers with CR2032 coin cell batteries installed, documentation"
                ],
                "headliner": [
                  "Lose your knack for losing things with the Apple AirTag!"
                ]
